Primary Key vs Foreign Key
Primary Key	                                            Foreign Key
Uniquely identifies each row	                  References a primary key in another table
Cannot contain duplicate values	                Can contain duplicate values
Cannot be NULL	                                Can be NULL (unless restricted)
One per table	                                  Multiple foreign keys can exist in a table


